HEADWORD: Flinty
<hw>Flint"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Flintier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Flintiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <def>Consisting of, composed of,
abounding in, or resembling, flint; <as>as, a <ex>flinty</ex> rock;
<ex>flinty</ex> ground; a <ex>flinty</ex> heart.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Flinty rock</b></col>, <it>or</it> <col><b>Flinty
state</b></col></mcol>, <cd>a siliceous slate; -- basanite is here
included. See <er>Basanite</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

